{
  "id": 5124331450138624,
  "name": "IndexedDB getAllRecords() and direction option for getAll()/getAllKeys()",
  "summary": "This feature adds the getAllRecords() API to IndexedDB's IDBObjectStore and IDBIndex.  It also adds a direction parameter to getAll() and getAllKeys().  This functionality enables certain read patterns to be significantly faster when compared to the existing alternative of iteration with cursors.  One key workload from a Microsoft property showed a 350ms improvement. \n\ngetAllRecords() effectively combines getAllKeys() and getAll() by enumerating both primary keys and values at the same time. For an IDBIndex, getAllRecords() also provides the record's index key in addition to the primary key and value.\n\ngetAllRecords() can optionally return records in either ascending or descending order.  This option is also back-ported to the existing operations getAll() and getAllKeys().",
